  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One of the frequent complex allele presentations is constituted by an inverted triplication flanked by duplications (DUP-TRP/INV-DUP).",
    "This allele is generated by a given pair of inverted LCRs telomeric to MECP2 being responsible for 20-30% of the MDS cases 6, a fraction of which will lead to a more severe clinical phenotype.",
    "When generated, this structure includes two breakpoint junctions (Jct) connecting the end of the duplication to the end of the triplication (Jct1) and the beginning of the triplication to the beginning of the duplication (Jct2).",
    "Given the presence of two breakpoint junctions in cis, the involvement of LCRs and the size of such events (often >500 kilobases (kb)), we lack the ability not only to detect this structure solely using long-read sequencing data but also to describe it after the VCF specification.",
    "Part of the complexity originates as the reads themselves only partially indicate the allele-for example, highlighting a shorter inversion 28."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
